# Student Presentation

## RL Engineering Tools: From Classical RL to LLM Agents

This directory contains the student-facing English presentation.

## Files

- [`slides.md`](slides.md) — GitHub-readable Marp slides.
- [`montage.svg`](montage.svg) — visual overview of the slide sequence.
- [`student-study-guide.md`](student-study-guide.md) — student review notes.

The editable PowerPoint is maintained separately and should be uploaded manually as `presentation/rl-engineering-tools-student-facing.pptx`.

A GitHub Actions workflow is included to render a PDF from `slides.md` when Actions write access is enabled.

## Learning objectives

Students should be able to describe the standard RL training loop, distinguish major engineering layers, compare representative classical RL libraries, and explain how LLM and agentic RL introduce rollout, synchronization, and scheduling problems.
